    "Manufacturers in these sectors face considerable fixed safety-related research and development costs, complicating the determination of an efficient standard of care in negligence cases (Daughety & Reinganum, 2013).",
    "The choice of liability rules may influence producers' incentives to embrace newer, safer technologies (Dari-Mattiacci & Franzoni, 2014).",
    "The literature has also extensively studied the incentive effects of durable precautions, which necessitate upfront investments to reduce the likelihood of accidents (Chen & Hua, 2012; Grady, 1987 Grady,, 2009;; Mot & Depoorter, 2011).",
    "Producers often need to make ongoing investments, such as enhancing the safety of autonomous vehicles.",
    "Therefore, the optimal liability regime should account for the impact of liability on these investment incentives.19 Building on Landes and Posner (1985), who list some of these and some different sources of product defect."
